<br>
They have something called humility.<br>
<br>
You see a ranger at a raid who is doing something useful, you see a player who is genuinely happy.  On raids, 90% of rangers will not complain about being the only one to buff an entire raid party, will complain about being the designated snarer (and a huge target), and will not complain about dying in general because of their class faults.<br>
<br>
Rangers have been through the darkness that is class prejudice, and they are mostly out now, and very happy to just be where they are.  Usually they fufill their purpose, and do it well and can be happy about that.<br>
<br>
For a while, rogues were the same way...We received brutal verbal and mental beatings for suffering through the dark ages of rogueliness (from release to about a year in), and once we got out and started accelling, we were just happy to do good.<br>
<br>
Then the twinks came.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I've wandered off track..<br>
<br>
Rangers are the best in game snarers, have class buffs that no one else can give you (that rock, and the casters never complain about handing them out), can compete with rogues for short term manaless damage dealing, and most importantly, are willing to do just about everything to help out a raid.<br>
<br>
Because its better than it used to be. <p><HR WIDTH="50%" ALIGN="LEFT"><IMG SRC="http://outside.clanpages.com/podside.jpg" ALIGN="left" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=100><br><b>Ullric Littleblade</b><br>Assassin of Tides of Valor<br><A HREF="http://www.thesafehouse.org">Ayonae Ro Ring Warden</A><BR>Master of the Jade Hand<BR><i><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=83046">"Speed kills if y'know what I mean."</A></i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utheperfectflaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThePerfectFlaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/18/01 11:26:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=598.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theperfectflaw.com/picture/jolly.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ranger's Life isn't Fair (serious read) :*(</span><hr size=1> I beg to differ.<br>
